==Cookies==
Of course you can work with cookies inside your Rails application. This is, again very similar to working with [[Ruby on Rails/ActionController/Parameters|parameters]] or [[Ruby on Rails/ActionController/Sessions|sessions]]. Consider the following example: <source lang=rails> def index #here we want to store the user name, if the user checked the "Remember me" checkbox with HTML attribute name="remember_me" #we have already looked up the user and stored its object inside the object-variable "@user" if params[:remember_me] cookies[:commenter_name] = @user.name else # Delete cookie for the commenter's name cookie, if any cookies.delete(:commenter_name) end end </source>
