I think the primary reasons English is easy to learn are:
#There are already a large portion of English speakers worldwide, foreign or not;
#It lacks a case systems in nouns (excluding pronouns), and verb conjugation is a lot simpler to memorize and adapt to (ratio is 1:50 for some!)
#It has a fairly flexible word order (there are more flexible ones, but those are because they have cases to allow it)
Latin derivations may be a reason but definitely not before those. Currently I'm learning Latin and the only things in my way are the lack of speakers/literary texts aimed at beginners, and the inflection of words. -- [[Special:Contributions/203.171.192.197|203.171.192.197]] ([[User talk:203.171.192.197|talk]]) 01:57, 10 June 2009 (UTC)

